      "id": "24ff8095cd49b1ee",
      "text": "Deterministic methods of SC has been developed to perform completely accurate computation with SC circuits.[19] The essential principle of these methods is that every bit of one bit-streams interacts with every bit of the other bit-streams exactly once. To produce completely accurate result with these methods, the operation must run for the product of the length of input bit-streams. Deterministic methods are developed based on unary bit-streams,[20][21] pseudo-random bit-streams,[22] and low-discrepancy bit-streams.[23] [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stochastic_computing#cite_note-19 wikipedia]"
