        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "19a70404024faf5b",
        "text": "Ward via matrix DM: Interesting. They describe stochastic signaling within a chip. In my application the signaling was between chips. I had to small functions: in and out. Both had an assumed sampling rate of approximately 6MHz or 16 microseconds per sample. In would read 256 samples and return the count of high samples. Out would set the threshold by which a random number would emit a high vs a low output. Outputs were pulses where each part would stop pulling high or low between pulses. This was effected by temporarily changing the output pin to be an input that was not read but essentially disconnected the output from other chips."
      },
